cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both this repository and the parent research program's pre-registration (OSF DOI 10.17605/OSF.IO/Q6JYN)."
title: "nerve-wml: Substrate-Agnostic Nerve Protocol for Inter-WML Communication"
abstract: >
  nerve-wml defines a substrate-agnostic communication protocol
  between World Model Language (WML) units. v1.1.0 validates THREE
  structurally distinct substrates (MlpWML stateless, LifWML spiking
  with surrogate gradient, TransformerWML attention-based) sharing
  the same Nerve Protocol. Empirical measurements: a four-point
  scaling law for the polymorphism gap (median 10.71 % at N=2 →
  6.71 % at N=16 → 2.39 % at N=32 → 2.73 % plateau at N=64; 15/15
  direction-stable seeds); direct inter-substrate information
  transmission with MI(codes_MLP, codes_LIF) / H = 0.91 at N=1
  strengthening to 0.96 at N=16 pool scale; round-trip fidelity
  MLP→LIF→MLP = 0.99; cross-substrate merge ratio = 0.97. These
  upgrade Claim B (substrate-agnostic information transmission)
  from architectural postulate to empirical finding. The repository
  also validates eleven gates (P, W, M, M2, Scale, Interp, Neuro,
  Dream-partial, Adaptive, LLM Advisor). Cited in the parent
  research program's Paper 1 §7.4 (dreamOfkiki cross-substrate
  validation).
